body.en-US:
In 2005 involved in the re-design of the National Lottery website, where I was building web pages to conform to WAI level 3 and W3C Standards

XHTML, CSS, Javascript

Lead front-end developer, for the complete re-design for the corporare site and the used cars site.

Responsible for creating .NET templates and intergrating flash elements; improving user experience, accessibility and SEO rankings. Ensuring W3C standards and cross browser testing.

XHTML, CSS, Javascript

Lead front-end developer for the re-design of Bowers and Wilkins website, responsible for creating .NET templates.

Improving user accessibility, SEO rankings and ensuring the site conforms to W3C Standards.

HTML, CSS3, Javascript, JQuery, .NET

Sony Gran Turismo Prologue 5 was the latest Sony Playstation game that was released in 2007; the new website was to aid in the product promotion.

I was involved in the front-end full life cycle of the project and the integration of the flash videos and blogs.

HTML, CSS, Javascript

Bowers & Wilkins Society of Sound is an additional new section to the Bowers and Wilkins main website.

As lead front-end developer, I was involved in the full life cycle of the project; which included building .NET templates, integrating blogs and other features to the site.

HTML, CSS, Javascript

UnionView was a new startup service - which involved providing information about different universities facilities throughout the UK. As lead front-end developer, I was responsible for building .NET templates, cross-browser testing and flash integration.

HTML, CSS, Javascript, XSLT

What Next? microsite for Terrence Higgins Trust. I was responsible for .NET and XSLT templating, CSS, cross-browser testing, accessibility and flash integration.

HTML, CSS, Javascript, XSLT

Lead front end developer - Complete website re-design, involved in the full life cycle using Agile methodologies, responsible for the .NET templating, cross-browser testing and accessibility.

HTML, CSS, Javascript

A brand new bingo website for ITV. Created templates, integrated the ITV player to get specific recorded show; which enabled users to watch them while playing bingo on the site.

XHTML, CSS, XML, Javascript, JQuery, PHP

A brand new site, newly designed for start up company Tea Shop and Film Company.

HTML5, CSS3

Lead developer on the project for the full life cycle of Force 4 re-design.

Updated existing templates to be W3C standards, added new features and functionality which were progressive enhancement. Worked closely with client and designers in a agile way to make iterative changes to certain features on the site.

HTML, CSS3, Javascript, JQuery, .NET

Lead front end developer - created templates for an adaptive responsive site. Involved in the full life cycle of the project, carried out cross browser testing for desktop and multiple mobile devices.

HTML5, CSS3, Javascript, JQuery

A freelance project, to re-design the City of London Choir site; which was built as mobile first, fully responsive to be viewed on tablet, mobile and desktop. Easy to maintain content by using a Content Management Tool Wordpress.

Responsibilities:

- Consultation with client, requirement gathering.
- Created flexible Wordpress templates
- Provided reusable templates, ease of use throughout the site.
- Cross browser testing on a variety of devices.
- Provided client with user documentation.
JQuery, Javascript, HTML5, CSS3, SASS, Wordpress, PHP

Visit website: https://cityoflondonchoir.org

You and Your Wedding, I was involved in the overhaul of the website re-design also transformation of the site to be responsive. In addition I worked on the prototype and live deployment of the mobile first application of you and your wedding venue finder.

Responsibilities:

- Archectituring the UI.
- Introducing and intergrating task runners Grunt.
- Incorporating the use SASS as part of the production process.
- Creating templates from designs.
- Cross browser testing on a variety of devices.
JQuery, Javascript, HTML5, CSS3, SASS, Bootstrap, Grunt

Visit website: http://www.youandyourwedding.co.uk/

Student.com a start-up company, a greenfield project to provide students a service and ability to search and book student accommodation near and around their universities from any in the world. Mainly starting with the UK market.

Key Responsibilities:

- Architecture UI with standards and guidelines.
- Building templates in PHP Symfony.
- Mobile first responsive website.
- Cross browser testing on a variety of devices.

Citizens Advice wanted to provide alternative solutions to give advice. So we provided various single page application that were self contained which provided decision tree like questions or bespoke calculators for situation such a budgeting.

Responsibilities:

- Architecturing UI and coding standards
- Building single page applications using React and Angular
- Unit Testing
- Bundling application using Webpack
- Web accessibilty
- Cross browser testing across a variety of devices.
JQuery, ES6, React, Angular, Webpack, Babel, Gulp, Jasmine

Visit website: https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk

Moola a fin-tech start-up company. Full website enhancements, new functionality and web accessibility.

React, Redux, Post-css, ES6

Visit website: https://moo.la

Built new features and components for the Comic Relief - Sport Relief campaign site.

Developed a new donation app for the main Comic Relief, this imporoved user experience and was made accessible to all by achieving the highest level2/3 WAI standards.

A greenfield project to develop a gameify app for Seda brand for the Brazilian market.

With: [Play Consulting](https://www.play-consult.co.uk/)

React greenfield project initial to build an app to represent market research data. The website brought together diverse data research in one place.

With: [Hugo & Cat](https://www.hugoandcat.com/en-gb/)
